{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0171h1jpe4BnQvbtiCwHPhxC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need to write a comprehensive change/migration plan. Let me summarize what I found:\n\n**Current State:**\n- RabbitMQ version: 3.12.14 (out of support release series)\n- Erlang/OTP: 25.3.2.15\n- Image: rabbitmq:3.12-management\n- 3 nodes, all running as disk nodes\n- No network partitions, no alarms\n\n**Virtual Hosts:**\n- `/` (default)\n- `/app`\n\n**Users:**\n- `admin` - [administrator] tag\n- `app-user` - no tags\n\n**Permissions:**\n- `/` vhost: admin has full access (configure/write/read: .*)\n- `/app` vhost: admin has full access; app-user has full access (configure/write/read: .*)\n\n**Queues and Exchanges:**\n- `/app` vhost has one classic durable queue called `app-queue` and only the standard AMQP exchanges (no custom ones)\n- All feature flags are enabled, including quorum and stream queues\n\nNow I'm thinking through the migration strategy. The version is out of support, so I need to plan an upgrade path that goes 3.12.14 → 3.13.x → 4.0.x following semantic versioning rules. The `app-queue` should be migrated from classic to quorum type since that's the production best practice and the feature flag is already available. I should also recommend adding policies for high availability, quorum configuration, and message TTL since none are currently set up.\n\nFor security, `app-user` has overly broad permissions — it can configure, write, and read on the /app vhost when it should only have write and read access. I'll also need to account for the Erlang version upgrade from 25 to 26, which is required for RabbitMQ 4.0. Both the 3.12→3.13 and 3.13→4.0 transitions support rolling upgrades, so there's flexibility in how to execute this.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_