ssic_mirrored_queue_version`, `classic_queue_type_delivery_support`, `maintenance_mode_status`.\n\n### 1.9 Enabled Plugins\n`rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s`, `rabbitmq_management_agent`, `rabbitmq_web_dispatch`, `amqp_client`, `cowboy`, `cowlib`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Identified Gaps and Risks\n\n| # | Area | Finding | Severity |\n|---|------|---------|----------|\n| G1 | Version | RabbitMQ 3.12 is **out of support** — no security patches | High |\n| G2 | Erlang | Erlang 25 is incompatible with RabbitMQ 4.x | High |\n| G3 | Queue type | `app-queue` is a **classic** queue — no replication, no raft-based durability | High |\n| G4 | Policies | No HA, TTL, dead-letter, or overflow policies configured | Medium |\n| G5 | Permissions | `app-user` has `configure=.*` on `/app` — can create/delete queues and exchanges | Medium |\n| G6 | Permissions | `admin` has full access to the default `/` vhost, which is otherwise unused | Low |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Proposed Changes\n\n### 3.1 Version Upgrade Path\n\nRabbitMQ requires sequential minor-version upgrades; skipping is not supported.\n\n```\n3.12.14  ->  3.13.x  ->  4.0.x  ->  4.1.x (latest stable)\n```\n\nEach hop is a **rolling upgrade** (one node at a time) with the cluster remaining operational.\n\n**Required Erlang upgrade:**\n- RabbitMQ 3.13+ requires Erlang 26+\n- Erlang upgrade must accompany the 3.12 -> 3.13 step (bundled in the new container image)\n\n**Container image sequence:**\n```\nrabbitmq:3.12-management  ->  rabbitmq:3.13-management\nrabbitmq:3.13-management  ->  rabbitmq:4.0-management\nrabbitmq:4.0-management   ->  rabbitmq:4.1-management  (if targeting latest)\n```\n\n**Pre-upgrade checklist (each hop):**\n1. Confirm all feature flags are enabled: `rabbitmqctl list_feature_flags`\n2. Enable any new flags introduced in the target version before rolling\n3. Review deprecation notices in the target release notes\n4. Export definitions as backup: `rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions.json`\n\n### 3.2 Queue Migration: Classic -> Quorum\n\n`app-queue` must be migrated from `classic` to `quorum` type. Classic queues have no built-in replication; a single-node failure can cause message loss.\n\n**Migration procedure (zero-downtime, requires application coordination):**\n1. Create a new quorum queue alongside the existing classic queue:\n   ```\n   rabbitmqctl declare_queue --vhost /app --name app-queue-new --type quorum --durable true\n   ```\n2. Update application publishers to dual-publish to both queues during the cutover window.\n3. Drain `app-queue` (classic) — wait for all in-flight messages to be consumed and acknowledged.\n4. Switch consumers to `app-queue-new`.\n5. Stop dual-publishing; delete `app-queue` (classic) once empty and idle.\n6. If the application uses a hard-coded queue name, recreate as `app-queue` (quorum type).\n\n**Quorum queue declaration arguments:**\n```json\n{\n  \"x-queue-type\": \"quorum\",\n  \"x-quorum-initial-group-size\": 3\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 Policy Additions\n\nApply the following policies to `/app` after the queue migration:\n\n| Policy Name | Pattern | Apply-to | Definition | Priority |\n|-------------|---------|---------|-----------|---------|\n| `message-ttl` | `^app-` | queues | `{\"message-ttl\":86400000}` (24 h TTL) | 0 |\n| `dead-letter` | `^app-` | queues | `{\"dead-letter-exchange\":\"amq.direct\",\"dead-letter-routing-key\":\"app-queue-dlq\"}` | 0 |\n| `overflow-drop` | `^app-` | queues | `{\"overflow\":\"drop-head\",\"max-length\":100000}` | 0 |\n\nAlso create a dead-letter queue `app-queue-dlq` (quorum, durable) to receive undeliverable/expired messages.\n\n### 3.4 Permission Hardening\n\n#### Restrict `app-user` on `/app`\nCurrent:  configure=`.*`  write=`.*`  read=`.*`\nProposed: configure=`^$`  write=`.*`  read=`.*`\n\nApplication services should publish and consume but must not create or delete queues/exchanges at runtime.\n\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"^$\" \".*\" \".*\"\n```\n\n#### Revoke `admin` access to `/` vhost (optional)\nThe default `/` vhost is unused. Revoking admin's permissions there reduces blast radius of credential compromise. Skip if any tooling relies on the default vhost.\n\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl clear_permissions -p / admin\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Execution Sequence\n\n### Phase 0 — Preparation (pre-change-window)\n1. Export cluster definitions as backup: `rabbitmqctl export_definitions /tmp/definitions-$(date +%Y%m%d).json`\n2. Confirm all three nodes are healthy: `rabbitmqctl cluster_status`\n3. Verify application can tolerate rolling restarts (connections re-establish within 30 s)\n4. Review RabbitMQ 3.13 and 4.x release notes for breaking changes\n5. Pre-pull new container images on all Kubernetes nodes to minimize pod restart delay\n\n### Phase 1 — Erlang + 3.12 -> 3.13 Rolling Upgrade\n1. Update StatefulSet image to `rabbitmq:3.13-management`\n2. Ensure `updateStrategy: RollingUpdate` with `maxUnavailable: 1`\n3. Watch each pod restart: `kubectl rollout status statefulset/rabbitmq`\n4. After each node rejoins, confirm 3 running nodes: `rabbitmqctl cluster_status`\n5. After all three nodes on 3.13: `rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all`\n\n### Phase 2 — 3.13 -> 4.0 Rolling Upgrade\n1. Verify all 3.13 feature flags are enabled\n2. Update StatefulSet image to `rabbitmq:4.0-management`\n3. Repeat rolling upgrade procedure from Phase 1\n4. Post-upgrade: `rabbitmqctl list_feature_flags` — confirm all flags enabled\n\n### Phase 3 — Queue and Policy Migration\n1. Create `app-queue-new` (quorum type) alongside existing `app-queue` (classic)\n2. Coordinate dual-publish cutover with application team\n3. Drain and delete `app-queue` (classic) once confirmed empty\n4. Apply policies listed in §3.3\n5. Apply permission restriction for `app-user` (§3.4)\n\n### Phase 4 — Validation\n1. `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` — 3 nodes running, no partitions, no alarms\n2. `rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app name type state` — queue shows type=quorum, state=running\n3. `rabbitmqctl list_policies -p /app` — policies present\n4. `rabbitmqctl list_permissions -p /app` — `app-user` configure column is `^$`\n5. Send and consume a test message end-to-end\n6. Export final definitions as a post-change snapshot\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\n| Phase | Rollback Action |\n|-------|----------------|\n| Phase 1 (3.12->3.13) | Not supported once a node boots on 3.13 and writes data. Mitigation: PVC snapshot + definitions export from Phase 0. |\n| Phase 2 (3.13->4.0) | Same constraint — forward-only. Restore from PVC snapshots if needed. |\n| Phase 3 (queue migration) | Classic `app-queue` remains until explicitly deleted; revert application to use it. |\n| Phase 4 (permissions) | Re-apply original: `set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` |\n\n**Key rollback constraint:** RabbitMQ does not support downgrading between minor or major versions once a node has joined the cluster on the newer version. The only full rollback path is restoring from PVC snapshots + the definitions export taken in Phase 0.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Change Window Recommendation\n\n| Step | Estimated Duration | Risk |\n|------|--------------------|------|\n| Phase 0 (preparation) | 30 min | None (read-only) |\n| Phase 1 (3.12->3.13 rolling) | 15-20 min | Low (rolling, cluster stays up) |\n| Phase 2 (3.13->4.0 rolling) | 15-20 min | Low |\n| Phase 3 (queue migration + policies) | 30-60 min | Medium (requires app coordination) |\n| Phase 4 (validation) | 15 min | None |\n| **Total** | **~2 hours** | |\n\nSchedule during a low-traffic window with the application team on standby for the Phase 3 queue cutover.\nPLANEOF","description":"Write plan.md to /tmp"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4120,"cache_read_input_tokens":36213,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4120},"output_tokens":50,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d869df13-242e-47bf-918e-365de1f8c76b","uuid":"6f091726-5bd4-4206-bbc9-23a341489012","request_id":"req_011CcPxeDdkPKD792BgnvjPT"}
